    reflection: "We've all lost people we were close to. While we were suffering from our grief, some well-meaning person tried to take our mind off it. However kind, these gestures are misguided.\n\nThe Stoics teach us to face, process, and deal with emotions immediately instead of running from them. Tempting as it is to deceive yourself or hide from a powerful emotion like grief, awareness and understanding are better. That's how one conquers grief."
